        "code": {
          "language": "markdown",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "# Employees API monitoring\nFocus: `/api/v1/employees` traffic. Micrometer stores the endpoint label as `/v1/employees` because the `/api` context path is stripped before metrics tagging.\n\nThis dashboard is ready for stress testing with throughput, latency, saturation, JVM, and connection-pool panels. True percentiles such as p95 and p99 will require HTTP histogram buckets to be enabled later.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "12.4.2",
      "title": "Usage Notes",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${datasource}"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "mappings": [],
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              }
            ]
          },
          "unit": "reqps"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 6,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 3
      },
      "id": 2,
